  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIf to delete 1-1 chat of the non-contact request the next time this contact sends a message it does not appear in Activity Center.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n1-1 chat re-appears in Activity Center upon the next message sent disregard when the 1-1 chat being deleted\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNo 1-1 chat in Activity Center upon the next message sent if this 1-1 chat of non-contact deleted from chat list\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) Create UserA and UserB\r\n2) UserA adds UserB in contacts\r\n3) UserA sends text message to UserB\r\n4) UserB opens Activity Center and taps on 1-1 contact request\r\n5) UserB taps `...` chat menu at top-right -> `Delete Chat`\r\n6) UserA sends text message to UserB again\r\n7) UserB verifies whether UserA's chat request appears in Activity Center\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly/release 0.14 \r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\nLogs: when received contact reuqest -> open 1-1 chat -> delete and UserA sends message again:\r\n[geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/6630785/geth.log)\r\n[Status.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/6630786/Status.log)\r\n",
